data.enText: to fasten or join one thing to another

data.chText: 把优惠券附在信的正面。
data.enText: Attach the coupon to the front of your letter.

data.chText: 我附上笔记一份供你参考。
data.enText: I attach a copy of my notes for your information.

data.chText: 我随电子邮件附上电子表格一份。
data.enText: I attach a copy of the spreadsheet (= send it with an email) .

data.chText: 他们在协议上附加了一些条件。
data.enText: They have attached a number of conditions to the agreement (= said that the conditions must be part of the agreement) .

texts: ~ importance, significance, value, weight, etc. (to sth)

data.chText: 认为有重要性（或意义、价值、分量等）；重视
data.enText: to believe that sth is important or worth thinking about

data.chText: 我认为这项研究十分重要。
data.enText: I attach great importance to this research.

data.chText: （有时不受欢迎或未受邀请而）参加，和…在一起，缠着
data.enText: to join sb for a time, sometimes when you are not welcome or have not been invited

data.chText: 在聚会上他老是缠着我，我简直无法摆脱他。
data.enText: He attached himself to me at the party and I couldn't get rid of him.
to be connected with sb/sth; to connect sth to sth

data.chText: 没有人指出这个产品可能会危害健康。
data.enText: No one is suggesting that any health risks attach to this product.

data.chText: 这事你一点责任也没有。
data.enText: This does not attach any blame to you.

simple_means.memory_skill: at 加强 + tach 钉；钉子 → 牢牢钉上 → 附上

means: 认为有重要性(或意义、价值、分量等)
(有时不受欢迎或未受邀请而)参加，和…在一起，缠着

ex.chText: 别忘了在申请表上贴一张近照。
ex.enText: Don't forget to attach a recent photograph to your application form.

ex.chText: 在那个小喇叭上装一节小电池。
ex.enText: Attach a small battery to the little loudspeaker.
Where is the attached reply slip?

synonyms.bx: 指将某物固定或连接到另一物上。

ex.enText: affix a stamp to the envelope

ex.chText: 这些标签应牢牢地贴在您的手提行李上。
ex.enText: These labels should be firmly affixed to your hand luggage.

synonyms.bx: 指把某物贴在另一物上，常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 合同中附加了保险条款。
ex.enText: An insurance policy was annexed to the contract.

ex.chText: 人们普遍认为财富未必能增添幸福。
ex.enText: It is widely accepted that happiness is not always annexed to wealth.

example: The spider's thread attached to the window sill

tr: take temporary possession of as a security, by legal authority
example: The customs agents impounded the illegal shipment
The police confiscated the stolen artwork
The grandparents want to bond with the child

value.def: If you attach something to an object, you join it or fasten it to the object.

example.ex: We attach labels to things before we file them away...
example.tran: 存档前，我们先贴上标签。

example.ex: The gadget can be attached to any vertical surface...
example.tran: 这小玩意儿可以粘在任何垂直表面上。

example.ex: The astronauts will attach a motor that will boost the satellite into its proper orbit...
example.tran: 宇航员们将安装一个发动机，以推动卫星进入正常运行轨道。

example.ex: For further information, please contact us on the attached form.
example.tran: 欲知详情，请使用所附表格联系我们。

value.def: If someone attaches himself or herself to you, they join you and stay with you, often without being invited to do so.

example.ex: Natasha attached herself to the film crew filming at her orphanage.
example.tran: 娜塔莎紧紧缠着在孤儿院拍摄电影的工作人员不放。

value.tran: （通常未受邀请而）加入，和…在一起，缠着

value.def: If people attach a quality to someone or something, or if it attaches to them, people consider that they have that quality.

example.ex: The authorities attached much significance to his visit.
example.tran: 当局非常重视他的访问。

example.ex: ...the magic that still attaches to the word 'spy'.
example.tran: “间谍”一词依然具有的神奇魅力

value.def: If you attach conditions to something such as an agreement, you state that specific things must be done before the agreement is valid.

example.ex: Activists are pressing the banks to attach political conditions to the signing of any new agreement...
example.tran: 激进分子强烈要求银行在签署任何新协议前要考虑政治条件。

example.ex: Magistrates will be able to attach conditions when juveniles are remanded.
example.tran: 地方法官将可以在少年犯送押时提出附加条件。

value.def: In computing, if you attach a file to a message that you send to someone, you send it with the message but separate from it.

example.ex: It is possible to attach executable program files to e-mail.
example.tran: 可以在电子邮件里附上可执行程序文件。

trans: 芯片贴装；固晶；芯片粘贴测试；芯片粘接；裸片粘接
添加数据库；附加数据库

partsOfSpeech.dec: at 加强 + tach 钉；钉子 → 牢牢钉上 → 附上
at 表加强 + tach 钉；钉子 + e → 背负国家使命〔的人〕→ 使馆随员
attach 附上；依恋 + ment 表名词 → 附件；附着
de 离开 + tach 钉；钉子 → 把钉上的分开 → 拆开
un 无 + attach 附上；依恋 + ed 表形容词 → 没有附加任何东西的 → 独立的

rootsaffixes.title: ab-, ac-, af-, ag-, ap-, ar-, as-, at-
